From: Jim Mattson <jmattson@google.com>
Date: Fri, 30 Sep 2022 00:51:58 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] KVM: x86: Mask off reserved bits in CPUID.80000001H
References: bsn#19
Patch-mainline: v5.10.154

commit 0469e56a14bf8cfb80507e51b7aeec0332cdbc13 upstream.

KVM_GET_SUPPORTED_CPUID should only enumerate features that KVM
actually supports. CPUID.80000001:EBX[27:16] are reserved bits and
should be masked off.

Fixes: 0771671749b5 ("KVM: Enhance guest cpuid management")
Signed-off-by: Jim Mattson <jmattson@google.com>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Paolo Bonzini <pbonzini@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Geliang Tang <geliang.tang@suse.com>
---
 arch/x86/kvm/cpuid.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/x86/kvm/cpuid.c b/arch/x86/kvm/cpuid.c
index b4f6d81c873f..06a776fdb90c 100644
--- a/arch/x86/kvm/cpuid.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kvm/cpuid.c
@@ -813,6 +813,7 @@ static inline int __do_cpuid_func(struct kvm_cpuid_array *array, u32 function)
 		entry->eax = min(entry->eax, 0x8000001f);
 		break;
 	case 0x80000001:
+		entry->ebx &= ~GENMASK(27, 16);
 		cpuid_entry_override(entry, CPUID_8000_0001_EDX);
 		cpuid_entry_override(entry, CPUID_8000_0001_ECX);
 		break;
